SIMPLE: inspector
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inspector
<hw>In*spect"or</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.: cf. F.
<ets>inspecteur</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who inspects, views,
or oversees; one to whom the supervision of any work is committed; one
who makes an official view or examination, as a military or civil
officer; a superintendent; a supervisor; an overseer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A police officer, typically holding a rank one below
superintendent, and in some cases in charge of several precincts;
<as>as, <ex>inspector</ex> Clousseau is investigating the
case</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Inspector general</b></col> <fld>(Mil.)</fld>, <cd>a
staff officer of an army, whose duties are those of inspection, and
embrace everything relative to organization, recruiting, discharge,
administration, accountability for money and property, instruction,
police, and discipline.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inspectorate</ent>⟦br⟧
